Fort Lauderdale, FL – R&B/Pop phenom, Halle Rae announces the release of her self-penned ‘NEW’ single ‘GHOSTED’. The sultry single features the grown-up Halle Rae, fondly remembered by her hometown fans for winning the popular Teen-Sensation Contest at the 2016 UNIFEST Multi-Cultural Festival, at the tender age of 15. Winning the top spot was a major accomplishment that fueled her desire to pursue a career as a professional singer/songwriter. When asked, what would you be doing if you were not creating and singing music? The young vocalist says, “I just cannot see myself doing anything else. There is nothing else I would rather do than produce music that makes my fans happy.” 2022 marks the year Halle Rae takes major steps towards making her dream a reality. With Ghosted now released, the young vocalist is focusing on writing songs and creating more content, highlighting her beautiful yet creative side and talent. July 1st, her loyal and newfound fans can find her single on iTunes, Tidal, Spotify and Amazon but rolling out on more platforms around the world each day.